on of the aesthetic potential of the transitory, independently of whether it manifests itself in fact or fiction. The methodological aim of the study is to demonstrate how fruitful a fusion of issues from literary and cultural studies can be.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aCannibalism in literature. 0aGerman literaturey19th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aGerman literaturey20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aImperialism in literature. 4aAltenberg, Peter / Ashantee. 4aEwers, Hanns Heinz / Die Mamaloi. 4aGrenzüberschreitung. 4aJünger, Ernst / Afrikanische Spiele. 4aKannibalismus ‹Motiv›. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Literary and Cultural Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110637854oZDB-23-GLC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2005z9783110277111oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK UND LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2005z9783110276886oZDB-23-DGA0 cprintz978348415109340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311094097840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110940978423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110940978/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGAb2005  aZDB-23-DGGb2005  aZDB-23-GLCc2000d2014